  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 21, 22.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - Punishment in its third degree. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "I will also send wild beasts among you, which shall rob you of your children, and destroy your cattle, and make you few in number.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " So in the case of the Assyrians transported to Palestine, \"At the beginning of their dwelling there, they feared not the Lord: therefore the Lord sent lions among them, which slew some of them\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 17:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "and your high ways shall be desolate.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 5:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"In the days of Shamgar the son of Anath, in the days of Jael, the highways were unoccupied, and the travelers walked through byways.\" Leviticus 26:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
